    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `nvim_create_autocmd`, args is only parsed to Lua callback, but not Vimscript callback\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create file `repro.vim` with this content\n```vim\nfunc! s:Callback(...)\n    echo a:0 -- number of arguments\n    echo a:1\nendf\n\ncall nvim_create_autocmd('BufRead', #{callback: expand('<SID>') . 'Callback'}\n```\n2. `$ nvim --clean -u repro.vim repro.vim`\n3. It prints '0', and following by an error saying `a:1 is undefined`)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should prints `1`, and then the dictionary `a:1`\n\nFor more context, this is the document\n\n```help\n                 â€¢ callback (function|string) optional: Lua function (or\n                   Vimscript function name, if string) called when the\n                   event(s) is triggered. Lua callback can return a truthy\n                   value (not `false` or `nil`) to delete the autocommand.\n                   Receives one argument, a table with these keys:\n                                                                  *event-args*\n```\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-1785+gb0bbe25c48\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKubuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nsnap",
    "closed_at": null,
