            "body": "Probably just a problem with help documentation, because as I can see, this is the first commit that introduces parsing args to callback https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/30bc02c6364f384e437a6f53b057522d585492fc, but it also only supported Lua callback, not Vimscript one. Also the function `call_autocmd_callback()` in that commit looks same as `au_callback()` in current Nvim src. \n\nAlso related to this commit https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/55a4aa41bb27aa9439fea11c4ebcfec2ee87844d\n\nSo @zeertzjq please change label of this issue to \"documentation\"",
